a-size-base 3: I will start by saying that my dog LOVES this. However, I specifically bought this because the original N-bones last him a long time, and this disappointed in me that regard. I literally gave this to my 4-month-old 40-lb boxer/hound puppy while I was in a meeting, thinking it would keep him busy but 5 minutes in he had already eaten one of the four sticks.So points for flavor and SoMe durability but I won’t be able to consider it a keep-him-busy chew; more like a slightly drawn out snack.

a-size-base: Good for a treat but not a long lasting chew
a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on June 21, 2022
a-size-base 3: Max, an 80 Ib Dalmatian/Great Pyrenees mix, enjoyed it but it didnt last longer than maybe 20 mins. He ate it like a treat rather than chewed it like a bone. Hoped this would work but nope, still on the hunt for a long lasting, non-nylon, non-rawhide, non-hard-as-a-rock chew bone!

a-size-base: Most expensive 15 minutes of dog fun EVER
a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on June 18, 2022
a-size-base 3: This quado was obviously very appealing to my dogs - I'd assumed they could gnaw on them for a half hour and then I'd put the rest away for another day.  How naive of me!  My older dog completely consumed this in the first 15 minutes, and the other had already consumed half of it.I was expecting a good after-dinner chew device and instead just got a bunch of very, very expensive extra calories.  Lesson learned - sorry, guys, I won't make the same mistake twice.  Do NOT recommend unless your dogs are very weak chewers.

a-size-base: A 10 minute treat never had a chance to be "interactive"
a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2022
a-size-base 3: I ordered the large for my 45 lb 6 year old mixed breed. Gave it to her while we opened our Christmas stockings. 10 minutes later, nothing was left except a stain on my rug. What part was interactive? Or worth the $10 "deal" I got on this?

a-size-base: Golden doodle finished it in 10 minutes
a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on September 3, 2023
a-size-base 3: My golden doodle (1year old) liked this chew, so much so that it was gone in 10 minutes. The chew is not challenging or long lasting for a big dog despite its advertising. So, it’s not at all worth the money. I was seriously shocked by how quickly it went. Won’t purchase again.

a-size-base: Not long lasting for aggressive chewers but dog loved the flavor while it lasted
a-size-base 2: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2023
a-size-base 3: I have a 20 lb. Cairn Terrier mix, I gave her this to occupy her on a 14 hour car ride. Keep in mind she did not chew it the entire time and by the time we arrived it was in 3 separate pieces.She did like the flavor, but durability is not its strong suit.She is a very aggressive chewer for her size, giving her lots of chew toys has kept her away from my furniture legs which she originally would naw on when she was a puppy.A little vicks vapor rub (buy the knock off from the $ store) on the legs of anything she was not supposed to chew on and supplying her with Nylabone chew toys for aggressive chewers has kept us all happy. (Just a little of the vapor rub works miracles, you do not have to slather it on)To wrap up, this is a good treat, but a few days at best. Dog approved the taste, she took it with her everywhere while it lasted.
